<p>have very good reason to hate them, they reckon they have a job to stop the French from killing them when they make them prisoner's. We travelled like lightning from 11.30 till 2.30 &amp; must have covered nearly 4 miles, the pace was terrific you could have picked baskets of flowers &amp; then boarded the train again. At last we pulled up &amp; over we went again to another big canteen, &amp; got some hot tea, fruit &amp; etc, the run from Roman' Camp we spent in 2nd class carriages, while the first part of the journey we done in old trucks so much for the budding officers we are doing well so far &amp; have</p>
